title: Incremental ICE in `exported_symbols` query

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Reproduction steps On repo : ``` git checkout 8f364cf cargo t -p toc_analysis --no-run git checkout 23b7440 cargo t -p toc_analysis -j1 --no-run ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.62.0-nightly (055bf4ccd 2022-04-25) binary: rustc commit-hash: 055bf4ccd521c2c2185166c86951be7be145727c commit-date: 2022-04-25 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.62.0-nightly LLVM version: 14.0.1 ``` Also hit on `rustc 1.61.0-beta.4 (69a6d12e9 2022-04-25)` and `rustc 1.60.0 (7737e0b5c 2022-04-04)` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'Found unstable fingerprints for mir_built(e82671bce93de738-864ce90ea73b0785): Steal { value: RwLock(RefCell { value: Some() }) }', compiler/rustc_query_system/src/query/plumbing.rs:626:9 ```
Backtrace
